==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Overhaul
<hw>O`ver*haul"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Overhauled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; p. pr. & vb. n.
<conjf>Overhauling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To haul or drag
over; hence, to turn over for examination; to inspect; to examine
thoroughly with a view to corrections or repairs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>To gain upon in a chase; to
overtake.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To repair thoroughly; to make repairs on; -- usually
implying major repairs and perhaps modifying improvements.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To overhaul a tackle</b></col>, <cd>to pull on the
leading parts so as to separate the blocks.</cd> -- <col><b>To overhaul
running rigging</b></col>, <cd>to keep it clear, and see that no hitch
occurs.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overhauling</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Overhaul</ent>⟦br⟧
